Our quantity of genes , after the new projections were lowered to 30,000 , is also no longer , by itself , a motive of pride for the species .
According to the Public Consortium , the human chromosomes and those of a mouse show a lot of similarities : there are at the minimum 200 segments with at least two common genes and in the same order .
